  </div>
  <h2 id="Introduction" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">Introduction</h2>
  <p style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 32px;">SonarQube is an open-source web-based tool for code quality analysis. SonarQube can analyze a wide range of code in different programming languages through plugins. This guide explains how to install SonarQube on Ubuntu 20.04 LTS.</p>
  <h2 id="Prerequisites" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 16px; list-style: none; padding: 0px; margin-left: 20px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px; position: relative; padding-left: 24px;">Deploy a&nbsp; <a href="https://www.vultr.com/docs/update-ubuntu-server-best-practices" style="touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--brand-primary); transition: color 0.3s ease 0s;">fully updated</a>&nbsp;Ubuntu 20.04 LTS server at Vultr with at least 2GB of RAM and 1 vCPU cores. </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px; position: relative; padding-left: 24px;">Create a&nbsp; <a href="https://www.vultr.com/docs/create-a-sudo-user-on-ubuntu-best-practices" style="touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--brand-primary); transition: color 0.3s ease 0s;">non-root user with sudo access</a>. </li>
  </ul>
  <h2 id="1__Install_OpenJDK_11" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">1. Install OpenJDK 11</h2>
  <ol style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; padding-left: 44px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">SSH to your Ubuntu server as a non-root user with sudo access.</li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Install OpenJDK 11.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo apt-get install openjdk-11-jdk -y
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <h2 id="2__Install_and_Configure_PostgreSQL" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">2. Install and Configure PostgreSQL</h2>
  <ol style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; padding-left: 44px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Add the PostgreSQL repository.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo sh -c ''echo "deb http://apt.postgresql.org/pub/repos/apt/ ``lsb_release -cs``-pgdg main" &gt;&gt; /etc/apt/sources.list.d/pgdg.list''
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Add the PostgreSQL signing key.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">$ wget -q https://www.postgresql.org/media/keys/ACCC4CF8.asc -O - | sudo apt-key add -
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Install PostgreSQL.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib -y
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Enable the database server to start automatically on reboot.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo systemctl enable postgresql
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Start the database server.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo systemctl start postgresql
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Change the default PostgreSQL password.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo passwd postgres
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Switch to the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">postgres</span>&nbsp;user. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">$ su - postgres
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Create a user named&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar</span>. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">$ createuser sonar
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Log in to PostgreSQL.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">$ psql
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Set a password for the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar</span>&nbsp;user. Use a strong password in place of&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px;">my_strong_password</code>. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">ALTER USER sonar WITH ENCRYPTED password ''my_strong_password'';
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Create a&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonarqube</span>&nbsp;database and set the owner to&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar</span>. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">CREATE DATABASE sonarqube OWNER sonar;
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Grant all the privileges on the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonarqube</span>&nbsp;database to the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar</span>&nbsp;user. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE sonarqube to sonar;
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Exit PostgreSQL.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">\\q
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Return to your non-root sudo user account.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">$ exit
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <h2 id="3__Download_and_Install_SonarQube" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">3. Download and Install SonarQube</h2>
  <ol style="padding-left: 44px;">
    <li style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Install the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">zip</span>&nbsp;utility, which is needed to unzip the SonarQube files. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo apt-get install zip -y
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Locate the latest download URL from the&nbsp; <a href="https://www.sonarqube.org/downloads/" style="touch-action: manipulation; color: var(--brand-primary); transition: color 0.3s ease 0s;">SonarQube official download page</a>. </p>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">Download the SonarQube distribution files.</p>
      <pre style="padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; border-radius: 3px;"><font color="#525666" face="monospace, monospace"><span style="font-size: 15px; white-space: normal;">sudo wget --no-check-certificate https://binaries.sonarsource.com/CommercialDistribution/sonarqube-developer/sonarqube-developer-9.4.0.54424.zip</span><span style="white-space: normal;"><br></span></font></pre></li><li style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 4px;">
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo unzip sonarqube-&lt;VERSION_NUMBER&gt;.zip
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Move the unzipped files to&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px;">/opt/sonarqube</code>&nbsp;directory </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo mv sonarqube-&lt;VERSION_NUMBER&gt; /opt/sonarqube
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <h2 id="4__Add_SonarQube_Group_and_User" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">4. Add SonarQube Group and User</h2>
  <p style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 32px;">Create a dedicated user and group for SonarQube, which can not run as the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">root</span>&nbsp;user. </p>
  <ol style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 32px; padding-left: 44px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Create a&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar</span>&nbsp;group. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo groupadd sonar
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Create a&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar</span>&nbsp;user and set&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">/opt/sonarqube</span>&nbsp;as the home directory. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo useradd -d /opt/sonarqube -g sonar sonar
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Grant the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar</span>&nbsp;user access to the&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px;">/opt/sonarqube</code>&nbsp;directory. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo chown sonar:sonar /opt/sonarqube -R
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <h2 id="5__Configure_SonarQube" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">5. Configure SonarQube</h2>
  <ol style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; padding-left: 44px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Edit the SonarQube configuration file.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo vim /opt/sonarqube/conf/sonar.properties
</code>
            </pre>
      <p style="margin-top: 28px;">Find the following lines:</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">#sonar.jdbc.username=
#sonar.jdbc.password=
</code>
            </pre>
      <p style="margin-top: 28px;">Uncomment the lines, and add the database user and password you created in Step 2.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sonar.jdbc.username=sonar
sonar.jdbc.password=my_strong_password
</code>
            </pre>
      <p style="margin-top: 28px;">Below those two lines, add the&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">sonar.jdbc.url</span>. </p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sonar.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/sonarqube
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Save and exit the file.</p>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Edit the sonar script file.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo vim /opt/sonarqube/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh
</code>
            </pre>
      <p style="margin-top: 28px;">About 50 lines down, locate this line:</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">#RUN_AS_USER=
</code>
            </pre>
      <p style="margin-top: 28px;">Uncomment the line and change it to:</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">RUN_AS_USER=sonar
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Save and exit the file.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <h2 id="6__Setup_Systemd_service" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">6. Setup Systemd service</h2>
  <ol style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; padding-left: 44px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Create a systemd service file to start SonarQube at system boot.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo vim /etc/systemd/system/sonar.service
</code>
            </pre>
      <p style="margin-top: 28px;">Paste the following lines to the file.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">[Unit]
Description=SonarQube service
After=syslog.target network.target

[Service]
Type=forking

ExecStart=/opt/sonarqube/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh start
ExecStop=/opt/sonarqube/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh stop

User=sonar
Group=sonar
Restart=always

LimitNOFILE=65536
LimitNPROC=4096

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Save and exit the file.</p>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Enable the SonarQube service to run at system startup.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo systemctl enable sonar
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Start the SonarQube service.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo systemctl start sonar
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Check the service status.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo systemctl status sonar
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <h2 id="7__Modify_Kernel_System_Limits" class="" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">7. Modify Kernel System Limits</h2>
  <p style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 32px;">SonarQube uses&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">Elasticsearch</span>&nbsp;to store its indices in an MMap FS directory. It requires some changes to the system defaults. </p>
  <ol style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 32px; padding-left: 44px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Edit the sysctl configuration file.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo vim /etc/sysctl.conf
</code>
            </pre>
      <p style="margin-top: 28px;">Add the following lines.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">vm.max_map_count=262144
fs.file-max=65536
ulimit -n 65536
ulimit -u 4096
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Save and exit the file.</p>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <p>Reboot the system to apply the changes.</p>
      <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">                <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo reboot
</code>
            </pre>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <h2 id="8__Access_SonarQube_Web_Interface" style="color: var(--docs-header); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; margin: 48px 0px 32px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 44px;">8. Access SonarQube Web Interface</h2>
  <p style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 32px;">Access SonarQube in a web browser at your server''s IP address on port 9000. For example:</p>
  <pre style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">        <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">http://192.0.2.123:9000
</code>
    </pre>
  <p style="color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 32px;">Log in with username&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px;">admin</code>&nbsp;and password&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px; margin-top: 32px;">admin</code>. SonarQube will prompt you to change your password. </p>
  <pre class="kl km kn ko ga md bt me" style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 56px; margin-bottom: 0px; background: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 20px;">        <span id="4f28" class="gj ld le ii mf b do mg mh l mi" data-selectable-paragraph="" style="box-sizing: inherit; display: block; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(41, 41, 41); line-height: 1.18; letter-spacing: -0.022em; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, &quot;Courier New&quot;, Courier, monospace; margin-top: -0.09em; margin-bottom: -0.09em; white-space: pre-wrap;">
            <span class="mf ij" style="box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;">sudo vim /opt/sonarqube/conf/sonar.properties</span>
        </span>
