<div class="resources__section" id="article_content" style="width: 1024px; position: relative; padding: 64px 0px 64px 64px; margin-bottom: 0px;">
  <div class="list-group list-group--collapse list-group--collapse-boxed list-group--icon m-b-7x mob-m-b-3x" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; border: 1px solid var(--docs-list-hover); overflow: hidden; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">
    <div class="list-group__item collapsed" data-toggle="lu-collapse" data-target="#using-different-system" style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; padding: 21px 24px 19px 72px; border: 1px solid rgb(230, 231, 235); position: relative; flex-direction: column; margin-bottom: 0px; border-radius: 4px; transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease 0s, border 0.3s ease 0s; cursor: pointer; box-shadow: none;">
      <div class="list-group__top top" style="flex: 1 1 auto; width: 860px; display: flex; align-items: center; cursor: pointer;">
        <h3 class="top__title h5 text-primary" style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-left: 0px; color: var(--docs-header); font-size: 19px; line-height: 24px; display: flex; flex-grow: 1; align-items: center; height: 24px; max-width: 100%; transition: all 0.45s ease 0s;">Using a Different System?</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h2 id="Introduction" class="" style="margin: 48px 0px 32px; color: var(--docs-header); font-weight: 500; font-size: 32px; line-height: 44px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Introduction</h2>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 32px; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Performing server administration as a non-root user is a best practice for security. After launching your Vultr VPS, your first task as root should be to set up a non-root user with sudo access.</p>
  <p style="margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 32px; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">This guide applies to the following versions:</p>
  <ul style="margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px; list-style: none; padding: 0px; margin-left: 20px; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">
    <li style="margin-top: 4px; position: relative; padding-left: 24px;">Ubuntu 20.04 LTS</li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px; position: relative; padding-left: 24px;">Ubuntu 19.10</li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px; position: relative; padding-left: 24px;">Ubuntu 18.04 LTS</li>
    <li style="margin-top: 4px; position: relative; padding-left: 24px;">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS</li>
  </ul>
  <h2 id="1__Add_a_New_User_Account" class="" style="margin: 48px 0px 32px; color: var(--docs-header); font-weight: 500; font-size: 32px; line-height: 44px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">1. Add a New User Account</h2>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 32px; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Create a new user account with the&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px;">adduser</code>&nbsp;command. Use a strong password for the new user. You can enter values for the user information, or press&nbsp; <kbd style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px; background-color: var(--docs-border); border: 1px solid rgb(82, 86, 102); border-radius: 3px; padding: 2px 6px; margin: 0px 2px; box-shadow: none;">ENTER</kbd>&nbsp;to leave those fields blank. </p>
  <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 15px; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">        <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo adduser sonarqube
Adding user ``sonarqube'' ...
Adding new group ``sonarqube'' (1001) ...
Adding new user ``sonarqube'' (1001) with group ``sonarqube'' ...
Creating home directory ``/home/sonarqube'' ...
Copying files from ``/etc/skel'' ...
New password:
Retype new password:
passwd: password updated successfully
Changing the user information for sonarqube
Enter the new value, or press ENTER for the default
        Full Name []: Example User
        Room Number []:
        Work Phone []:
        Home Phone []:
        Other []:
Is the information correct? [Y/n] y
</code>
    </pre>
  <h2 id="2__Add_the_User_to_the_Sudo_Group" class="" style="margin: 48px 0px 32px; color: var(--docs-header); font-weight: 500; font-size: 32px; line-height: 44px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">2. Add the User to the Sudo Group</h2>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 32px; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Add the new user to the sudo group.</p>
  <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 15px; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">        <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo adduser sonarqube sudo
</code>
    </pre>
  <h2 id="3__Test" class="" style="margin: 48px 0px 32px; color: var(--docs-header); font-weight: 500; font-size: 32px; line-height: 44px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">3. Test</h2>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 32px; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Switch to the new user.</p>
  <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 15px; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">        <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">sudo su - sonarqube
</code>
    </pre>
  <p style="margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 32px; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Verify you are the new user with&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px;">whoami</code>, then test sudo access with&nbsp; <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: inherit; background-color: var(--docs-border); color: var(--docs-code); padding: 0.25em 0.5em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-radius: 25px; margin-top: 32px;">sudo whoami</code>, which should return&nbsp; <span style="color: var(--docs-header);">root</span>. </p>
  <pre style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 15px; padding: 9px 16px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: var(--docs-tags); border: none; color: rgb(82, 86, 102); white-space: normal; border-radius: 3px;">        <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">$ whoami
sonarqube
$ sudo whoami
[sudo] password for sonarqube:
root
</code>
    </pre>
  <div>
    <code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; background: transparent; padding: 0px; border-radius: 25px; white-space: pre;">
      <br>
    </code>
  </div>
</div>','2022-04-29 09:51:53',1);
